Recommended where a condensate plume from the flue might cause a nuisance, the terminal should be positioned outside a building with the air inlet facing down and outlet connection facing upwards. The outlet must be at least 45° to the wall with the 'peak' uppermost to avoid rain entering the opening. It must be installed at least 2m above ground level and be secured.
